comments: Anunoby (TOR) extends his leg out slightly into Adebayo (MIA), causing marginal contact to occur after his release.
VanVleet (TOR) turns into Butler's (MIA) lower body as he is airborne, affecting his body's trajectory on the shot attempt.
Strus (MIA) retreats in Anunoby's (TOR) path and absorbs body contact before legally dislodging the ball during the driving shot attempt.
Herro (MIA) does not bring his left hand completely under the ball during his dribble.
Strus (MIA) establishes his left foot as his pivot foot and maintains it before the start of his dribble.
Achiuwa (TOR) moves alongside Strus? (MIA) path and absorbs body contact during the driving shot attempt.
Lowry (MIA) initiates contact with Siakam?s (TOR) arms, which affects his upward shooting motion for the driving shot attempt.
Butler (MIA) releases the inbounds pass within five seconds.

Anunoby (TOR) and Herro (MIA) both simultaneously have their hands on the ball. As Anunoby makes contact with the ball, a jump ball is whistled and the whistle occurs prior to any ensuing arm or body contact with Herro.
Lowry (MIA) is inbounds when he legally saves the ball.
Anunoby (TOR) and Adebayo (MIA) both make a play for the loose ball, and incidental body contact occurs that results in Adebayo on the floor.
Herro (MIA) releases the inbounds pass within five seconds.
Vincent (MIA) and Trent Jr. (TOR) make incidental knee-to-knee contact as Vincent attempts to get open for the inbounds pass.
Siakam (TOR) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Lowry?s (MIA) driving shot attempt.

Adebayo (MIA) extends his left forearm into Achiuwa's (TOR) side and dislodges him from his position as the latter attempts to reach for the inbounds pass. The contact occurs after Anunoby (TOR) releases the ball.
Adebayo (MIA) is imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Butler (MIA) gathers the ball on his left foot and establishes his right foot as his pivot, which he maintains.
Vincent (MIA) retreats in Siakam's (TOR) path and absorbs the body contact before Siakam releases the pass, and the contact is incidental.
Siakam (TOR) commits a take foul on Butler (MIA).
Lowry (MIA) briefly rests a slight hand on Siakam?s (TOR) side before removing it during the drive, and marginal contact occurs.
Butler (MIA) moves through Achiuwa's (TOR) back, affecting his put-back shot attempt.
